==English==

===Alternative spellings===
*[[pretence]] ''(Only correct spelling in the US)''

===Noun===
'''pretense'''

# A false or [[hypocritical]] profession, as, under ''pretense'' of friendliness; [[sham]], [[pretext]], [[claim]], as without pretense of accuracy.

===Synonyms===
*[[sham]] ''a [[substitution]], [[imitation]] or [[counterfeit]] purporting to be the real thing''
*[[affectation]] ''denotes [[deception]] for the sake of [[escape]] from punishment or an awkward situation''
*[[subterfuge]]